This is a Next.js 16 App Router project with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4,
and Supabase.

Tech stack:
- Next.js 16 App Router (NOT pages router — never use pages/)
- Tailwind CSS v4 (no tailwind.config.js — config is in CSS directly)
- Supabase for DB, Auth (SSR), and Storage
- shadcn/ui for UI components
- @dnd-kit/core for drag and drop on the kanban board
- recharts for charts (always loaded via next/dynamic)
- zod for input validation on all server actions
- sonner for toast notifications
- cmdk for the command palette
- lucide-react for icons
- vitest for tests

Architecture rules:
- Data fetching: server components only (no useEffect + fetch)
- Mutations: server actions only (no API routes for mutations)
- Before every mutation, call:
    SET LOCAL app.current_team_member_id = '<uuid>'
  using the service role client so the change_history trigger knows who acted
- Never use the service role key in client components or browser code
- RLS is enabled on all 15 tables — always test with a real auth session
- Use the generated types from src/lib/types/database.ts
- Never write raw SQL strings — use the Supabase JS client query builder

Two user personas:
- Team members: authenticate via /login, use routes under app/(app)/
  their auth_user_id maps to team_members.auth_user_id
- Client portal users: authenticate via /portal/login, use app/(portal)/
  their auth_user_id maps to client_users.auth_user_id
  RLS automatically scopes all their queries to their client_id

File structure:
- src/app/(app)/         internal team app
- src/app/(portal)/      client-facing portal
- src/app/(auth)/        login pages
- src/lib/supabase/      server.ts, client.ts, service.ts
- src/lib/types/         database.ts (generated), index.ts (aliases)
- src/lib/actions/       server actions grouped by domain
- src/lib/notifications.ts   notification helpers
- src/lib/storage.ts     Supabase Storage helpers
- src/lib/dashboard-bridge.ts  typed queries for dashboard_api views
- src/components/ui/     shadcn components
- src/components/        shared app components

Database (15 tables):
attachments, change_history, client_users, clients, interactions,
milestones, notifications, project_members, project_sections, projects,
task_comments, task_dependencies, tasks, team_members, time_entries

No GHL integration. No invoicing. Clients are created manually.